social_posts.post_text:
Little life update for the homies: I’ve been back in Minnesota for 2 months now and it’s good to be home! There’s always ups and downs, but I’m still choosing to make things fun! Ice fishing season has officially started, Minnesota Vikings are going crazy, and it’s so nice being able to hang with my Midwest people 
🍻🏈🎣 

I just started looking through photos and videos from this last season @simply_stargazing and I spent in Yosemite and I’m probably gonna start posting them on here! It’s not easy being away from the mountains and all of the amazing people we met in the valley, but I’m so damn thankful for the experiences and friendships that came out of there! 

Hope ya’ll are doing good and are continuing to enjoy this beautiful life each and every day! One step at a time to reach the summit 🥾🏔

Look at all these mountain people

The people you hangout with in the valley are same people that live right next to you and and go to the same job in the morning! It’s a really cool community to be a part of and it keeps things fun 24/7. 

Counting down the days to jump back into the top rope parties, bouldering sessions, and half dome street barbecues 🕺🏻

Happy birthday Jas!! I hope you know how amazing you are! You have the kindest and most loving spirit AND you can literally climb mountains! I love you so much! Thanks for being you 😍 @simply_stargazing

“Misconceptions” is up on Spotify and Apple Music! (Links in my bio) 🎶 

I recently revived an old project of mine and decided to share it with ya’ll! Publicly releasing music is a fun and scary feeling, but I’m putting this out there in hopes that at least one person can connect with it 🖤 if you have a few minutes, play it in the background of your day, or crank the volume and throw some personal lyrics on it! Make it yours! 

Little life story:
I’m just a dude that uses a guitar to guide me through a lot of things in life. By no means do I claim this track to be a masterpiece, but I can tell you that it meant a lot to me when I was strumming those strings. This one feels like a song trapped in time because when I first made it, I was hung up on that strong feeling of not receiving any closure. Now that some years have passed, I’m able to revisit those feelings with the same heart, but a new perspective. So here it is! Previously titled “Memories” and now “Misconceptions” 

Enjoy!! 🖤
Man.. I love Minnesota winters, but I can’t wait to climb some rocks this summer! Scrolling through my phone and found this picture from Yosemite ☀️🏞️
Finding more reasons to love you every single day! You are my sunshine, Jas ♥️ happy Valentine’s Day!
There’s half dome looking all dreamy again 🤩
Well.. I’m a Toyota guy now! Been on the hunt for a while and finally found the Rav4 I’ve been looking for. Let the adventures begin!

Jasmin and I recently celebrated our 3 year anniversary! Our journey together has definitely been wild and exciting! It’s so fun looking back at all of the incredible memories we’ve made together and I love how we’ve only continued to build upon that! 

I’m beyond thankful for every second spent with you @simply_stargazing ❤️😍 Everything about you is beautiful and I love you with all my heart!

Happy birthday, Jasmin!! 

This girl is SO special! Her joy and kindness continues to grow every year and I’m so thankful for all the time I get to spend with her ❤️

Love you so much @simply_stargazing! Thank you for your loving heart and adventurous spirit!

Adventuring and making music along the way!
